================================================================================
Build / development dependencies
================================================================================

SentinelQA depends on a large number of Python and TypeScript libraries
at build/test time (Playwright, axe-core, Typer, Pydantic, httpx, uv,
pnpm, ruff, mypy, pytest, eslint, prettier, vitest, commitlint,
pre-commit, gitleaks, ts-morph, Jinja2, BeautifulSoup, and others).
Each is governed by its own upstream LICENSE, distributed alongside
the package via the package manager. The aggregated build-time
inventory (with pinned versions) is produced by the supply-chain
module (`sentinel supply-chain sbom`, Phase 33) and lives under
`.sentinel/runs/<run-id>/sbom.cdx.json`.

================================================================================
Adding a new vendored upstream
================================================================================

If you vendor a new file under `packages/shared-schema/external/` (or
anywhere else in the tree that does not inherit the root LICENSE):

  1. Add the file's source URL + upstream license to the
     "Vendored upstream schemas" section above.
  2. Register the file in
     `scripts/release/audit_license_headers.py`'s
     `VENDORED_EXTERNALS` map.
  3. Run `make audit-license-headers`; the audit fails until both
     bullets are done.

See `docs/dev/ownership.md` for the broader attribution procedure.
